y the SCT concepts that they have become familiar with. We hear from learners, teachers and researchers in a variety of languages, contexts, ages and proficiencies. Intended for graduate and undergraduate audiences, this new edition of the textbook includes controversies in the field, improved questions for collaborative discussion and provides updated references to important work in the literature of second language teaching, learning and research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakersxSocial aspects. 0aLanguage and culture. 0aSecond language acquisitionxSocial aspects. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aVygotsky.  aZone of Proximal Development.  aactivity theory.  alanguaging.  anarratives.  asecond language learning.  asecond language teaching.  asociocultural theory.1 aKinnear, Penny, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSteinman, Linda, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060670640uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178309318240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781783093182423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781783093182/original  a978-3-11-060670-6  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK